Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
load_timing_debug_report(25.10)                load_timing_debug_report(25.10)

Name
       load_timing_debug_report  -  Loads  the violation report in Innovus for
       debugging timing results

Syntax
       load_timing_debug_report

       [-help]

       [-name report_name]

       [{-proto [-additional_slack_past_wns <number>]  [-num_path <number>]}]

       [-num_path]

       <filename>

       Loads the violation report in Innovus for debugging timing results.

       The violation report that you specify using  the  load_timing_debug_re-
       port command has a special output binary format, which you can generate
       through  the  binary  value of the report_timing -output_format command
       parameter.  Alternatively,  you  can  also  generate  it  through   the
       timeDesign -timingDebugReport parameter. For more information on creat-
       ing  path categories, see the 'Creating Path Categories' section in the
       Debugging Timing Results chapter of the Innovus User Guide document.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each load_timing_debug_report parameter.

              For  a  detailed  description of the command and all its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man load_timing_debug_report

       <filename>
              Specifies the name of the timing debug file, also known  as  the
              violation report.

       -name  Specifies  the  report  name to load the machine readable timing
              report files incrementally.

              Note: The name can be specified using any string; it is not  the
              file name.

       -num_path
              Specifies  the  number  of  paths to be reported in the detailed
              path violations.

       {-proto [-additional_slack_past_wns number]  [-num_path number]}
              Creates flex model categories and displays the top path  of  the
              top  8  (by default) categories. This option can be used for de-
              sign that has flexModels.

              Use -additional_slack_past_wns to report all  paths  with  slack
              worst than (WNS and additional specified slack value).

              Use -num_path to control the number of violation paths.

Examples:
              * The following command loads the machine readable timing report
                top.btarpt:

                load_timing_debug_report top.btarpt

              * The  following  commands  load two machine readable timing re-
                ports top1.btarpt and top2.btarpt together:

                load_timing_debug_report -name default_report top1.btarpt

                load_timing_debug_report -name default_report top2.btarpt

                Global  Timing  Debug  (GTD)  will  first  load   the   report
                top1.btarpt, then append top2.btarpt incrementally to the cur-
                rent report.

Related Information
       The Timing Budgeting chapter of the Innovus User Guide document.

